    {
      "id": "9adffdf1_88604602",
      "file_path": "healthcheck-container/get-status.js",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 153,
      "message": "You're reading it correctly.\n\nThe Kubernetes API documentation is unclear about what happens if the \"limit\" parameter is not provided.  The documentation that I found doesn't say if there's a default limit.  I put in the limit parameter and set it to a high value as a defense against the possibility that there was a relatively small default value. (The documentation does say that \"some servers\" might not honor the limit and will send everything regardless of the limit setting.)  It's possible that leaving off the limit would give everything--I just didn't find a clear statement to that effect.\n\nThe healthcheck is used in the integration testing environment to validate that DCAE has come up properly.  1000 deployments won't happen in that environment, at least not intentionally.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 511,
        "name": "Jack Lucas",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jflos@sonoris.net",
        "username": "jackl"
      },
